HEADWORD: Soft-finned
<hw>Soft"-finned`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having the fin rays cartilaginous or flexible; without spines; --
said of certain fishes.</def>⟦br⟧
